  "body": "If a transaction reverts with an encoded `Error(string)` (e.g., `require(false, \"some reason\");`, then the error thrown should _always_ include that message.\r\n\r\nThis should happen even if there are no sources, or the optimizer is enabled, or anything else. There isn't an scenario where we can't do this. Right now it's not happening sometimes (see for example https://github.com/NomicFoundation/hardhat/issues/3940) because there's some issue in our error inferrer.",
